WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.571
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.637 --> 00:11.578
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.645 --> 00:14.581
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.647 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.418
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.485 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.426
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.493 --> 00:29.429
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.965 --> 00:33.266
- [grunting]

00:33.333 --> 00:37.137
{\an1}- Princess, don't you want
to help Daddy steer?

00:37.203 --> 00:39.072
{\an1}With both of us using
our energy

00:39.139 --> 00:41.741
{\an1}we might be able to make it
back to the shoreline.

00:41.808 --> 00:43.576
{\an1}[groans]

00:43.643 --> 00:44.811
- No, I'm good.

00:44.878 --> 00:47.280
I'm gonna keep streaming
this show.

00:47.347 --> 00:48.415
[baby giggling]

00:48.481 --> 00:49.482
Huh?

00:49.549 --> 00:51.484
[baby giggling]

00:51.551 --> 00:52.619
- Hmm.

00:52.685 --> 00:53.787
- All done.

00:53.853 --> 00:55.889
{\an3}- [gasps]
It's beautiful!

00:55.955 --> 00:57.490
Thank you, Mother.

00:58.758 --> 00:59.759
- Hello, Mummy!

00:59.826 --> 01:01.227
Oh.

01:01.294 --> 01:02.128
Mummy?

01:02.195 --> 01:04.897
I'm gonna call you back.

01:04.964 --> 01:08.935
{\an3}- Daddy, how come
everyone else's dad is a woman?

01:09.002 --> 01:11.504
- Sweetie, those are moms.

01:11.571 --> 01:13.106
- Oh, right.

01:13.173 --> 01:15.008
I want one of those!

01:15.074 --> 01:16.376
I want one of those! Gimme!
- Oh, dear. No.

01:16.443 --> 01:17.877
- Gimme! I want one, now!
- Don't do that.

01:17.944 --> 01:19.546
Daughter. Plea--please!
- Daddy!

01:19.612 --> 01:20.680
<i>[yelling]</i>

01:20.747 --> 01:23.683
<i>[quirky music]</i>

01:23.750 --> 01:29.689
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:31.324 --> 01:33.860
- Sun salutations, child.

01:33.927 --> 01:35.228
- Morning, Dr. Roberts.

01:35.295 --> 01:37.297
{\an1}Dad sent me over to borrow
a cup of sugar.

01:37.363 --> 01:40.266
{\an3}- I don't keep processed poisons
in my home,

01:40.333 --> 01:44.037
{\an3}but I do have
weighted pebbles.

01:44.103 --> 01:45.839
- Are these healthier?

01:45.905 --> 01:47.874
{\an3}- No, but they do
taste awful.

01:47.941 --> 01:50.076
- Silent protest!

01:51.244 --> 01:53.379
Silent protest!

01:54.514 --> 01:57.183
I want a mom!
Ah! I want a mom!

01:57.250 --> 01:59.719
{\an1}- But Princess,
you have a mother.

01:59.786 --> 02:01.154
{\an1}See?

02:01.221 --> 02:04.224
{\an1}This mass of enchanted crystals
represents your mother

02:04.290 --> 02:07.393
before she ascended
our physical realm.

02:07.460 --> 02:10.830
And this shrine is here
for your maternal needs.

02:10.896 --> 02:12.465
What more could you want?

02:12.532 --> 02:14.934
- Ah!
You don't get it, Daddy!

02:15.001 --> 02:16.769
{\an3}- You know,
I just realized,

02:16.836 --> 02:18.838
{\an3}it's really inappropriate
for me to be--

02:18.905 --> 02:21.574
- Daddy, is the crystal shrine
gonna throw spritzer

02:21.641 --> 02:23.743
on the paparazzi
at my first wedding?

02:23.810 --> 02:26.346
Is the crystal shrine gonna
take me handbag shopping

02:26.412 --> 02:28.214
after I settle
my first divorce?

02:28.281 --> 02:30.950
No! It won't!
Sassy hair flip.

02:31.017 --> 02:33.152
{\an1}- [groans]
You're right.

02:33.219 --> 02:37.457
{\an1}Well, what my sweetie wants,
my sweetie shall have.

02:37.524 --> 02:40.426
- Good, then it's settled.
You're gonna start dating now!

02:40.493 --> 02:43.162
{\an1}- I'm actually
a pretty incredible matchmaker.

02:43.229 --> 02:45.832
{\an1}One time, Dade was
looking for a sweater,

02:45.899 --> 02:48.268
{\an1}and then I found him
a sweater.

02:48.334 --> 02:50.236
<i>[pleasant music]</i>

02:50.303 --> 02:52.438
Ladies, thank you
for coming today.

02:52.505 --> 02:54.307
{\an1}You're all here for a chance
to win a date

02:54.374 --> 02:56.309
with our eligible bachelor.

02:56.376 --> 02:59.479
An expert in crystal healing,
a proud father,

02:59.546 --> 03:01.915
and owner
of a full head of hair--

03:01.981 --> 03:03.917
Dr. Roberts.

03:03.983 --> 03:05.785
- Ooh!

03:05.852 --> 03:08.688
- I'm Tara. I'm a hairdresser
and I scream in my sleep.

03:08.755 --> 03:13.226
- I'm Hanzi, and sometimes
the moon talks to me.

03:13.293 --> 03:16.996
- I came here to dispute
a parking ticket from 1994.

03:17.063 --> 03:19.566
- Let's get this game started!

03:19.632 --> 03:22.569
<i>[pleasant music]</i>

03:22.635 --> 03:25.305
- Oh. Dating. Yay.

03:25.371 --> 03:27.106
- Okay, Mrs. Hanzi,

03:27.173 --> 03:30.243
this first question is
a little personal.

03:30.310 --> 03:35.448
What is...your favorite type
of food?

03:35.515 --> 03:37.684
- My favorite food
is anything that is made

03:37.750 --> 03:39.252
with love and intention.

03:39.319 --> 03:41.421
- Dad, what'd you answer?
- Oh, darn.

03:41.487 --> 03:44.257
{\an3}Well, I wrote
food made with anger.

03:44.324 --> 03:46.459
- Wha--
- Oh, well, not a match.

03:46.526 --> 03:51.064
- Okay, Ms. Tara,
this question is pretty risqué.

03:51.130 --> 03:54.801
What is your favorite color?

03:54.867 --> 03:56.202
Hoo hoo hoo!

03:56.269 --> 03:57.870
- Um, I don't know, purple?

03:57.937 --> 03:59.372
- Incompatible,
not a match.

03:59.439 --> 04:00.840
[buzzer sounds]
- Gimme!

04:00.907 --> 04:04.277
You wrote violet.
That's just fancy purple!

04:04.344 --> 04:08.414
- Violet is very different
than regular purple.

04:08.481 --> 04:10.950
Polar opposites
vibrationally,

04:11.017 --> 04:12.752
{\an3}and, uh--oh, oops.
Mm.

04:12.819 --> 04:15.355
{\an3}The answer card is
in my mouth. [chuckles]

04:15.421 --> 04:18.391
- Our next question is
for Randl's mom.

04:18.458 --> 04:22.729
Uh, Foo, I can't ask this.
It's disgusting.

04:22.795 --> 04:24.897
- Well, I wanna to know
the answer!

04:24.964 --> 04:26.966
{\an3}- I drew a horse
with no teeth.

04:27.033 --> 04:30.236
{\an3}Everyone off my waterbed,
I'm going to sleep now.

04:30.303 --> 04:32.038
{\an3}[snoring]

04:32.105 --> 04:35.174
{\an3}Oh.
[snores]

04:35.241 --> 04:37.176
- What a shame.
We tried our best.

04:37.243 --> 04:38.444
I guess
there's no matches here.

04:38.511 --> 04:41.381
Let's go inside and
drink boba tea.

04:41.447 --> 04:43.016
- Daddy, wait, come back.

04:43.082 --> 04:44.717
[both groan]

04:44.784 --> 04:47.687
{\an1}- Excuse me, I saw
that dating profile.

04:47.754 --> 04:49.856
Am I too late to meet
the eligible bachelor?

04:49.922 --> 04:53.660
- Um, well, as you can see,
it's boba time now, so--

04:53.726 --> 04:55.895
- Ooh! I love boba.

04:55.962 --> 04:57.330
{\an1}They feel like
little eyeballs.

04:57.397 --> 04:58.765
- Um, who are you?

04:58.831 --> 05:01.467
{\an1}- Professionally,
I'm a mail order mom,

05:01.534 --> 05:03.069
but you can call me Evelyn.

05:03.136 --> 05:06.572
{\an3}- Oh, man, Evelyn is awesome.
She taught me how to sew.

05:06.639 --> 05:09.609
{\an1}- Hey, kiddos.
Those two are sweeties.

05:09.676 --> 05:11.044
{\an3}- Hmm.

05:11.110 --> 05:13.379
Daddy, you're taking this lady
out on a date.

05:13.446 --> 05:15.381
She has major wife potential.

05:15.448 --> 05:19.252
{\an3}- Uh, b-b-but I thought we
concluded there were no matches.

05:19.318 --> 05:22.455
{\an3}But I-I--
[groans]

05:22.522 --> 05:24.390
{\an3}Oh.

05:30.563 --> 05:33.433
{\an3}- Your daughter's room is
very cute.

05:33.499 --> 05:35.668
{\an3}I have to ask
about the crystals.

05:35.735 --> 05:36.803
You have so many.

05:36.869 --> 05:38.404
{\an1}- Oh, yes,
they mostly help

05:38.471 --> 05:40.540
{\an1}with blood impurities
and cholera.

05:40.606 --> 05:42.909
{\an3}- Ooh!
I love that kind of stuff.

05:42.975 --> 05:45.411
{\an3}Did you know if you leave
a sapphire under your pillow--

05:45.478 --> 05:47.914
{\an1}- It'll purify
your mind sphere and...

05:47.980 --> 05:50.817
both: Connect you
with your past selves.

05:50.883 --> 05:51.984
- Yes! [laughs]

05:52.051 --> 05:55.421
{\an3}- Oh. Sorry,
I'm-I'm rambling.

05:55.488 --> 05:58.357
{\an3}It's been a really long time
since I dated.

05:58.424 --> 05:59.425
What about you?

05:59.492 --> 06:01.427
Well, since my wife passed,

06:01.494 --> 06:06.032
{\an1}I've poured all my focus
into raising my ray of sunshine.

06:06.099 --> 06:07.800
- Oh, I didn't know.

06:07.867 --> 06:10.937
- Hey! I've been spying on you
for an hour.

06:11.003 --> 06:12.171
What's the hold up?

06:12.238 --> 06:13.206
[rope breaks]
[screams]

06:13.272 --> 06:14.507
[grunts]

06:14.574 --> 06:17.343
Evelyn, you live here now!
Dad, marry her!

06:17.410 --> 06:20.680
{\an1}- Sweetie, I'm trying
to make you happy.

06:20.747 --> 06:21.914
I-I just need some--

06:21.981 --> 06:22.915
- Enough talk.

06:22.982 --> 06:24.050
Hi-yah!

06:24.117 --> 06:25.752
- Daughter!
- Lock it down!

06:25.818 --> 06:27.320
Put a ring on it!

06:27.386 --> 06:30.189
- I...I...I...

06:30.256 --> 06:31.424
I can't do this!

06:31.491 --> 06:35.328
- Hey!
- [sobbing]

06:35.394 --> 06:37.997
- Uh, Dad?
- [sobbing]

06:38.064 --> 06:40.066
- Fine! I give up!

06:40.133 --> 06:42.068
I'll just never have a mom.

06:42.135 --> 06:43.870
[door closing]

06:43.936 --> 06:46.973
[munching]

06:47.039 --> 06:49.475
{\an1}- Yoo-hoo.
Do you wanna talk?

06:49.542 --> 06:52.078
{\an1}I know stress eating
when I see it.

06:52.145 --> 06:54.347
{\an1}You must really miss
your mom, huh?

06:54.413 --> 06:55.882
- We never talk about her.

06:55.948 --> 06:58.584
Dad is always acting like
talking to crystals helps.

06:58.651 --> 07:00.720
Like, she's just not here.

07:00.787 --> 07:02.722
{\an1}- Your mother is here
right now.

07:02.789 --> 07:04.524
{\an3}- Are you gonna tell me
she's in my heart?

07:04.590 --> 07:06.859
{\an3}Look, I'm eating off the floor
right now.

07:06.926 --> 07:10.229
{\an1}- No, no, it sounds silly,
but it's true.

07:10.296 --> 07:12.932
{\an1}You don't need a new mom
or some crystals.

07:12.999 --> 07:15.134
You just need yourself.

07:15.201 --> 07:17.270
- Hm.

07:17.336 --> 07:19.705
{\an1}- You just focus and
close your eyes.

07:19.772 --> 07:22.275
I'll give you some privacy.

07:22.341 --> 07:24.944
- Okay, Zen.

07:25.011 --> 07:26.846
[groaning]

07:26.913 --> 07:28.981
Ohh!

07:30.283 --> 07:31.584
What the--

07:31.651 --> 07:35.688
Ew, what is this place,
a sample sale?

07:35.755 --> 07:36.489
Huh?

07:36.556 --> 07:38.291
<i>[ethereal music]</i>

07:38.357 --> 07:39.592
- Mom?

07:39.659 --> 07:41.794
- That's right, baby.

07:41.861 --> 07:44.297
'Tis I, MC Queen.

07:44.363 --> 07:46.299
Do you like what I did
with the place?

07:46.365 --> 07:48.734
- This is fabulous.

07:48.801 --> 07:51.504
Uh, there's so much
I want to ask you.

07:51.571 --> 07:53.573
{\an1}- We can talk about anything
you like,

07:53.639 --> 07:56.342
{\an1}but first,
give Mommy a twirl.

07:56.409 --> 07:57.910
{\an1}Ooh-whoo!

07:57.977 --> 08:00.580
- I call this one
my peekaboo look.

08:00.646 --> 08:03.850
- You inherited
my gorgeous shoulders, baby.

08:03.916 --> 08:06.586
{\an1}Now, tell me why
you're upset.

08:06.652 --> 08:08.521
- Ugh! Where to begin?

08:08.588 --> 08:10.823
{\an3}I told Dad he needs
to start dating again

08:10.890 --> 08:13.192
{\an3}but he's being all weird
and crying.

08:13.259 --> 08:16.128
{\an1}- Well, he's gonna have
a hard time replacing me.

08:16.195 --> 08:17.530
I'm pretty incredible.

08:17.597 --> 08:19.732
I have four credit cards.

08:19.799 --> 08:23.269
- I don't wanna wait!
I want a mom now!

08:23.336 --> 08:24.737
{\an1}- Darling.

08:24.804 --> 08:27.540
{\an1}Now, you remember
when you were five months old

08:27.607 --> 08:29.375
and you were devastated

08:29.442 --> 08:31.744
{\an1}because your favorite baby spa
burned down?

08:31.811 --> 08:34.013
- Rejuvenation Spa Junior.

08:34.080 --> 08:35.881
They did kelp facials.

08:35.948 --> 08:38.451
- And you needed time
to deal with that loss

08:38.517 --> 08:41.486
{\an1}before you were ready to find
a new baby spa, right?

08:41.554 --> 08:43.089
{\an3}- Oh, yeah.

08:43.155 --> 08:44.290
{\an1}See, baby?

08:44.357 --> 08:47.093
{\an1}Your dad needs some time
to heal too.

08:47.159 --> 08:49.929
{\an1}He'll be ready to find
someone new one day.

08:49.996 --> 08:51.030
{\an3}- Promise?

08:51.097 --> 08:52.531
- I promise.

08:52.598 --> 08:53.633
- I miss you, Mom.

08:53.699 --> 08:55.935
- I miss you too, baby.

08:56.002 --> 08:58.771
{\an1}You know I'll always
be here with you.

08:59.672 --> 09:01.507
- Oh, hey, I'm floating.

09:01.574 --> 09:03.109
- Oh, it's time to go, dear.

09:03.175 --> 09:05.912
If you stay any longer
you'll go into cardiac arrest.

09:05.978 --> 09:08.014
- Good-bye, Mom!

09:08.080 --> 09:09.415
- I love you!

09:09.482 --> 09:12.018
- I love you too-oo!

09:13.219 --> 09:14.253
[gasps]

09:14.320 --> 09:15.488
[coughs]

09:15.554 --> 09:16.756
- Dr. Roberts?

09:16.822 --> 09:18.891
You've been in there
a while.

09:18.958 --> 09:20.259
Are you all right?

09:20.326 --> 09:24.563
{\an3}- Sorry, it seems
my tear chakra was surging.

09:24.630 --> 09:27.400
{\an1}- I understand.
I think I'd better go.

09:27.466 --> 09:28.634
{\an3}- Uh, wait.

09:28.701 --> 09:31.570
{\an3}I want to make my daughter
happy, so...

09:31.637 --> 09:33.572
{\an3}when should we schedule
the wedding?

09:33.639 --> 09:35.074
- Everybody shut up!

09:35.141 --> 09:36.776
I have something to say.

09:36.842 --> 09:40.446
[stuttering]
I can't--uh--

09:40.513 --> 09:41.714
[groans]

09:41.781 --> 09:43.649
- What is it, dear?

09:43.716 --> 09:46.152
- [groans]
I can't say it with words.

09:46.218 --> 09:48.220
Just watch this.

09:48.287 --> 09:49.221
[funk music playing]

09:49.288 --> 09:50.556
- ♪ Ha! Ugh! ♪

09:50.623 --> 09:53.192
♪ Cappuccino machine
Cappuccino ♪

09:53.259 --> 09:57.463
- Princess, you're expressing
your feelings through dance.

09:57.530 --> 09:59.398
Why, it's as clear as day.

09:59.465 --> 10:00.866
- ♪ Cappuccino machine ♪

10:00.933 --> 10:04.003
{\an1}- You mean to say
you've had a vision?

10:04.070 --> 10:07.306
And now you understand
that I need more time

10:07.373 --> 10:08.808
{\an3}before I'm ready
to date again.

10:08.874 --> 10:11.210
{\an1}- You're getting all this
from her dancing?

10:11.277 --> 10:12.912
{\an1}- And you want
a maternal figure,

10:12.979 --> 10:15.581
{\an1}but not at the expense
of my feelings?

10:15.648 --> 10:18.617
{\an1}Darling, this is
very mature of you.

10:18.684 --> 10:19.719
- ♪ Ha, cappuccino ♪

10:19.785 --> 10:23.022
- ♪ Ha, cappuccino machine ♪

10:23.089 --> 10:26.559
{\an1}- Oh, you dance as gracefully
as your mother did.

10:26.625 --> 10:29.295
{\an1}She could
really break it down.

10:29.362 --> 10:31.163
- Yeah, she was the best.

10:31.230 --> 10:32.565
- Oh, I love you, dear.

10:32.631 --> 10:35.568
{\an3}- Love you too,
but say it, don't spray it.

10:35.634 --> 10:37.403
- I'm glad you two made up.

10:37.470 --> 10:39.038
I think I better
head home now.

10:39.105 --> 10:41.841
- Evelyn, I'm sorry
about tonight.

10:41.907 --> 10:43.476
You're a lovely woman.

10:43.542 --> 10:45.211
- Hey, don't worry about it.

10:45.277 --> 10:48.748
And Princess, if you ever want
someone to take you shopping,

10:48.814 --> 10:50.916
you let me know, okay?

10:50.983 --> 10:52.051
{\an3}- Really?

10:52.118 --> 10:54.587
{\an3}I mean, maybe I will,
whatever.

10:54.653 --> 10:56.055
- I made you some cookies.

10:56.122 --> 10:58.124
{\an1}When you're ready
to date again

10:58.190 --> 10:59.558
give me a call.

10:59.625 --> 11:01.761
Oh. I will.

11:01.827 --> 11:05.297
Uh, wait!
I didn't get your phone number.

11:05.364 --> 11:06.899
{\an3}- Duh!
Daddy, look.

11:06.966 --> 11:09.602
- Oh, how clever of her to leave
her number in such a--

11:09.668 --> 11:11.170
- Do these have chocolate?
- Wait, dear,

11:11.237 --> 11:13.139
<i>I haven't memorized</i>
<i>all the numbers yet!</i>

11:13.205 --> 11:14.774
<i>- [munching]</i>

11:16.842 --> 11:18.277
- Thanks for coming,
everyone.

11:18.344 --> 11:20.246
I'm sorry to keep
you junior artists waiting,

11:20.312 --> 11:22.748
but since we're busting out
the markers this week,

11:22.815 --> 11:25.785
I took some extra precautions
to keep us stain proof.

11:25.851 --> 11:28.821
{\an1}- Uh, do I really
have to wear all this?

11:28.888 --> 11:31.023
- Yeah, Kratz,
you're the sloppiest one here.

11:31.090 --> 11:32.224
- Really?
- Oh, yeah, definitely.

11:32.291 --> 11:33.426
- Well, yeah.

11:33.492 --> 11:34.760
- Okay, good to know.

11:34.827 --> 11:37.863
- Perfect.
As soon as I get my smock on,

11:37.930 --> 11:41.333
I'll be ready to get...
messy.

11:41.400 --> 11:43.569
- Oh, ho, ho, you are bad.

11:44.437 --> 11:45.371
- Huh?

11:45.438 --> 11:46.739
Hm.

11:46.806 --> 11:48.941
I could've sworn I had it
right here.

11:49.008 --> 11:51.343
Hey, Dade, did you take my--
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

11:51.410 --> 11:52.378
{\an1}Come on, Harvey,
what are you saying?

11:52.445 --> 11:53.913
Like, I'm the kind of guy

11:53.979 --> 11:55.915
{\an1}who just goes through your stuff
when you're not looking

11:55.981 --> 11:58.284
{\an1}just to find out
what it smells like?

11:58.350 --> 12:01.754
{\an3}- I was sure I had it.
I'll check upstairs.

12:03.789 --> 12:06.759
Oh, hey, Miche-e-e-l-l-l-e.

12:06.826 --> 12:09.428
<i>[ominous music]</i>

12:09.495 --> 12:11.163
Wait a second.

12:11.230 --> 12:13.532
Is that my smock?

12:13.599 --> 12:15.634
{\an1}Did you cover it
in spaghetti?

12:15.701 --> 12:18.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:18.537 --> 12:20.439
{\an1}[grumbles]

12:20.506 --> 12:23.442
<i>[heavy metal music]</i>

12:23.509 --> 12:30.449
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:30.516 --> 12:31.884
Okay. No problem.

12:31.951 --> 12:33.619
I always keep
a pair of overalls handy

12:33.686 --> 12:35.087
if the smock is
in the wash.

12:35.154 --> 12:37.523
Moving on.
Let's take roll call.

12:37.590 --> 12:38.657
Huh?

12:38.724 --> 12:39.992
Where'd my clipboard go?

12:40.059 --> 12:41.260
- [babbling]

12:41.327 --> 12:44.063
{\an3}[grunting]

12:44.130 --> 12:45.631
- [groans, sighs]

12:45.698 --> 12:48.467
{\an1}Dad! Can you do something
about Michelle?

12:48.534 --> 12:50.136
- In here, son!

12:50.202 --> 12:51.203
{\an3}- Dad?

12:51.270 --> 12:52.471
- H-hey, buddy.

12:52.538 --> 12:53.906
{\an1}Looks like
our little baby angel

12:53.973 --> 12:56.142
{\an1}accidently locked me
in her crib. [chuckles]

12:56.208 --> 12:58.410
{\an1}She's a little handful,
isn't she?

12:58.477 --> 13:00.479
- Oh, she's somethin'!

13:00.546 --> 13:01.947
{\an1}- [chuckles]
Anyway, glad you found me.

13:02.014 --> 13:03.482
- Can you--
- Sorry, Dad,

13:03.549 --> 13:04.984
gotta call Mom real quick.

13:05.050 --> 13:06.886
{\an1}Oh.
Okay.

13:06.952 --> 13:09.288
- Maybe Mom can come do
something about Michelle.

13:09.355 --> 13:11.724
<i>[phone ringing]</i>

13:11.790 --> 13:13.759
Why isn't she picking up?

13:14.693 --> 13:18.697
[phones ringing and buzzing]

13:19.565 --> 13:21.267
[grumbles]

13:22.568 --> 13:24.036
- Is everything okay?

13:24.103 --> 13:26.505
- Oh, yeah. It's fine.

13:26.572 --> 13:28.040
[chuckles]

13:28.107 --> 13:30.142
I'll just pass around
the signup sheet later.

13:30.209 --> 13:32.077
Now, let's inspire
each other

13:32.144 --> 13:34.713
by looking at our work
from last week.

13:35.915 --> 13:38.184
Wow. Look at those.

13:38.250 --> 13:41.387
I cannot believe
how talented my friends are.

13:42.821 --> 13:44.223
I don't know about you,

13:44.290 --> 13:46.659
but I feel like I had
an artistic breakthrough.

13:46.725 --> 13:47.760
Huh?

13:47.826 --> 13:49.562
My drawing!

13:49.628 --> 13:52.431
Miche-e-e-lle!

13:52.498 --> 13:53.899
{\an1}[grumbles]

13:53.966 --> 13:58.037
I'm so--I just--
[groans]

13:59.171 --> 14:01.574
Huh? What? Ugh!

14:01.640 --> 14:03.108
What is this thing?
[bump throbbing]

14:03.175 --> 14:06.312
- I know exactly what that is.
You've got rage.

14:06.378 --> 14:09.582
Join the club, my siblings
make me rage all the time.

14:09.648 --> 14:10.649
See?
[bump throbbing]

14:10.716 --> 14:12.551
- Oh. Yeah, me too.

14:12.618 --> 14:13.919
I rage quietly.

14:13.986 --> 14:15.521
I'm good at hiding it.
[bump throbbing]

14:15.588 --> 14:17.823
- Wait, really?
Even you, Piri?

14:17.890 --> 14:20.125
- The sun provides
both beautiful light

14:20.192 --> 14:22.328
and intense, scorching heat!

14:22.394 --> 14:24.863
- How do I get rid of it?
Should I push it down?

14:24.930 --> 14:26.532
{\an3}- No!
That's dangerous.

14:26.599 --> 14:29.268
{\an3}If you push your rage down
you might explode.

14:29.335 --> 14:31.070
{\an3}I heard that's what happened
to Kratz.

14:31.136 --> 14:33.005
{\an1}That's why we don't
see him anymore.

14:33.072 --> 14:34.506
- I'm right here.

14:34.573 --> 14:36.508
- Poor, poor Kratz.

14:36.575 --> 14:37.876
- Oh, my gosh!

14:37.943 --> 14:40.613
{\an1}I had no idea everyone was
so enraged.

14:40.679 --> 14:43.182
{\an1}We should not have to live
like this.

14:43.249 --> 14:47.620
{\an1}If only there was a way
to cage this rage.

14:47.686 --> 14:48.988
[pleasant music playing]

14:49.054 --> 14:50.522
Welcome, fellow ragers.

14:50.589 --> 14:53.792
Now, we're all here
because we're furious!

14:54.660 --> 14:56.295
Ahem. Anyways,

14:56.362 --> 14:59.031
I think if we could just
all talk out our issues,

14:59.098 --> 15:01.200
we can stop feeling so mad
all the time.

15:01.267 --> 15:02.835
- Oh, uh, excuse me.

15:02.901 --> 15:05.838
{\an3}I'm a mad scientist,
so technically,

15:05.904 --> 15:08.574
I'm more--crazy!
Than angry.

15:08.641 --> 15:09.742
Can I stay?

15:09.808 --> 15:12.745
{\an1}- Sure.
Okay, who wants to go first?

15:12.811 --> 15:14.446
Okay, Claire, go for it.

15:14.513 --> 15:17.850
{\an1}Oh.
Uh, are you okay, Harvey?

15:17.916 --> 15:19.785
- Yeah. Why?

15:19.852 --> 15:22.354
Oh. Don't mind
my furrowed eyebrows.

15:22.421 --> 15:24.390
It's just a side effect
of my rage.

15:24.456 --> 15:25.424
Please carry on.

15:25.491 --> 15:26.892
- Um, okay.

15:26.959 --> 15:29.928
So, I guess a lot of things
really make me flip my lid.

15:29.995 --> 15:32.665
{\an1}Like, how I'm so busy
all the time.

15:32.731 --> 15:35.701
{\an1}But if I'm not, then my mom
won't be proud of me,

15:35.768 --> 15:37.069
and that stinks.

15:37.136 --> 15:38.904
And my sister gets
all the attention

15:38.971 --> 15:41.073
because "she's perfect."

15:41.140 --> 15:43.842
{\an1}But I mean,
I guess she is perfect.

15:43.909 --> 15:45.878
- Okay, we get it.

15:45.944 --> 15:47.980
{\an3}Sisters are garbage,
big deal.

15:48.047 --> 15:50.349
{\an1}- Hey, hey, you don't know
what it's like.

15:50.416 --> 15:51.617
Siblings are the worst!

15:51.684 --> 15:52.985
{\an1}- Wow, Dade. [chuckles]
So interesting

15:53.052 --> 15:54.520
{\an1}how I had my hand up
before you

15:54.586 --> 15:56.255
{\an1}and yet you're the one
who gets to comment.

15:56.322 --> 15:58.824
- Okay, let's just calm down
everyone.

15:58.891 --> 16:01.493
{\an1}- Anyways, as I was saying,
my sister--

16:01.560 --> 16:04.496
- Hey, what is with that tone?
You know, I was defending you.

16:04.563 --> 16:07.032
{\an3}- Can't we talk
about <i> my</i> problems?

16:07.099 --> 16:08.767
I have several.

16:08.834 --> 16:10.703
- How about we talk about
how none of you

16:10.769 --> 16:12.938
make eye contact
when you talk to me?

16:13.005 --> 16:15.107
- I'm just blocking
all you haters.

16:15.174 --> 16:16.308
Blocked!

16:16.375 --> 16:18.444
- I was the first
to raise my hand.

16:18.510 --> 16:20.713
I did everything right!

16:20.779 --> 16:24.316
- I've got a theory
that the moon is a woman.

16:24.383 --> 16:27.052
- Uh, guys, one at a time.
[all talking at once]

16:27.119 --> 16:29.188
Come on, listen, everyone.

16:29.254 --> 16:31.857
If we just--
[groans]

16:31.924 --> 16:33.225
[all talking at once]
Whoa. What?

16:33.292 --> 16:34.293
[growls]

16:34.360 --> 16:38.097
Everyone shut your pie holes!

16:38.163 --> 16:39.298
[gasps]

16:40.866 --> 16:42.134
I'm sorry, everyone.

16:42.201 --> 16:43.936
{\an3}I don't know
what came over me.

16:44.002 --> 16:45.270
- But Harvey, look.

16:45.337 --> 16:48.407
{\an1}Is it just me, or did your rage
lose some juice?

16:48.474 --> 16:51.076
{\an3}- You're right,
I think shouting helped.

16:51.143 --> 16:53.812
Hey, everyone,
try screaming!

16:53.879 --> 16:55.514
{\an1}- Hey, maybe don't tell me
what to do!

16:55.581 --> 16:57.216
{\an3}- Well, it's working,
isn't it?

16:57.282 --> 16:58.917
{\an1}- Yes, actually,
thank you!

16:58.984 --> 17:00.085
I feel much better!

17:00.152 --> 17:01.353
- Good! I'm glad!

17:01.420 --> 17:03.889
- Um, what are we
supposed to yell about?

17:03.956 --> 17:06.125
{\an3}- Anything!

17:06.191 --> 17:07.326
{\an1}- Okay.

17:07.393 --> 17:09.595
[screaming]

17:09.661 --> 17:11.497
- I know what I'm gonna
scream about--

17:11.563 --> 17:14.532
how uncomfortable
these dang chairs are!

17:14.599 --> 17:15.867
<i>[heavy metal music]</i>

17:15.934 --> 17:18.936
- Yeah! Stab it in the face
with your fist!

17:19.003 --> 17:20.472
Wow, this is wonderful!

17:20.539 --> 17:23.008
{\an3}I'm really starting to feel
relieved!

17:23.075 --> 17:25.243
{\an3}- Hey, sweetie, what are you
shouting about?

17:25.310 --> 17:27.479
{\an1}Everything!
Thanks for asking!

17:27.546 --> 17:30.783
{\an3}- Awesome!
I love a good holler!

17:30.849 --> 17:33.852
{\an3}But seriously, you guys can't
scream in the library.

17:33.919 --> 17:35.821
{\an1}- Can we be loud and
destructive elsewhere?

17:35.888 --> 17:37.656
- Of course, sweetie.

17:37.723 --> 17:39.658
[all screaming and yelling]

17:39.725 --> 17:42.661
<i>[heavy metal music]</i>

17:42.728 --> 17:44.396
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:44.463 --> 17:47.299
- Wait a minute,
this is my house.

17:47.366 --> 17:49.835
- Wow, great meeting,
everyone.

17:49.902 --> 17:52.704
I feel good knowing
we could all leave here today

17:52.771 --> 17:54.506
with a little less rage.

17:54.573 --> 17:56.875
[all agreeing at once]

17:56.942 --> 17:59.044
♪ Doot doot
dealing with my anger ♪

17:59.111 --> 18:01.280
♪ Doot doot
dooby dooby dooby dooby ♪

18:01.346 --> 18:03.882
[sighs]
My bedroom,

18:03.949 --> 18:05.984
one of my favorite rooms
in the house.

18:06.051 --> 18:10.122
[humming]

18:11.790 --> 18:13.459
Bu--bu--bu--

18:13.525 --> 18:14.927
b-bu--b-bu--

18:14.993 --> 18:16.161
b-b-bu--

18:16.228 --> 18:18.730
b-b-bu--bu--bu--bu--

18:18.797 --> 18:19.998
[groans]

18:20.065 --> 18:22.935
[slowly rising scream]

18:23.001 --> 18:24.503
[baby babbling]

18:24.570 --> 18:25.604
- Michelle!

18:25.671 --> 18:28.073
{\an1}You keep ruining
my personal property!

18:28.140 --> 18:30.809
{\an1}How about I ruin
some of yours?

18:30.876 --> 18:32.177
{\an1}[grunts]

18:32.244 --> 18:33.178
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:33.245 --> 18:40.385
[prolonged scream]

18:43.922 --> 18:47.493
[panting]

18:47.559 --> 18:50.462
{\an1}- Harvey, we all heard
your enraged distress call.

18:50.529 --> 18:51.563
- [growling]

18:51.630 --> 18:52.865
- Michelle's rattle.

18:52.931 --> 18:54.967
{\an1}[gasps]
Do it, Harvey.

18:55.033 --> 18:57.436
{\an3}- There's nothing else
left to do.

18:57.503 --> 18:58.871
- Let your rage out.

18:58.937 --> 19:01.707
{\an1}She wrecked your stuff,
you wreck hers.

19:01.773 --> 19:03.876
That's justice.

19:03.942 --> 19:06.712
- [grunting]

19:06.778 --> 19:10.582
- I'm sorry, Michelle,
but this is justice!

19:10.649 --> 19:11.984
[groans]

19:12.918 --> 19:15.587
[cheers and laughter]

19:15.654 --> 19:18.824
<i>[ominous music]</i>

19:18.891 --> 19:20.592
- There.

19:20.659 --> 19:22.094
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:22.160 --> 19:24.596
- [grumbling]

19:24.663 --> 19:27.332
- Oh. Oh. Lookit!
She's got the rage too.

19:27.399 --> 19:31.737
Michelle, you must release
your darkness.

19:31.803 --> 19:37.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:37.109 --> 19:38.944
- [groans]

19:39.011 --> 19:41.680
[screaming]

19:44.816 --> 19:46.118
- No!

19:46.184 --> 19:47.819
My gummies!

19:47.886 --> 19:51.490
{\an3}You ripped the pocket
where I keep my vitamin gummies!

19:51.557 --> 19:55.193
{\an3}How am I supposed to be
a healthy boy

19:55.260 --> 19:57.996
without my vitamins?

19:58.063 --> 19:59.364
- [blows raspberry]

19:59.431 --> 20:01.233
- [growling]

20:01.300 --> 20:04.036
all: Fight! Fight!
Fight! Fight!

20:04.102 --> 20:06.805
{\an1}- Wait, are you even allowed
to fight babies?

20:06.872 --> 20:08.440
- Technically, no.

20:08.507 --> 20:10.309
all: Fight! Fight!
Fight! Fight!

20:10.375 --> 20:14.246
{\an1}- Harvey! Michelle!
Time for dinner!

20:14.313 --> 20:16.715
{\an1}I can see you playing
on that distant plateau

20:16.782 --> 20:18.116
with my binoculars!

20:18.183 --> 20:21.320
{\an1}Anyways, hurry home!
Love you!

20:22.254 --> 20:25.390
<i>[ominous music]</i>

20:25.457 --> 20:27.859
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:27.926 --> 20:30.862
- Sure feels a little tense
at the dinner table tonight.

20:30.929 --> 20:33.298
{\an3}- Is everything okay
between you two?

20:33.365 --> 20:34.733
{\an7}- Yup!

20:35.901 --> 20:37.302
{\an1}- Eep!

20:37.369 --> 20:38.704
- Well, whatever happened,

20:38.770 --> 20:42.341
{\an3}just remember that you two
are family.

20:42.407 --> 20:45.110
{\an3}- Tend to your anger
as you would tend to each other,

20:45.177 --> 20:47.446
with love, with care.

20:47.512 --> 20:48.814
- Where did that come from?

20:48.880 --> 20:50.515
- It's on the back
of the juice box.

20:53.118 --> 20:56.054
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:56.121 --> 20:58.056
- [growling]

20:58.123 --> 21:05.263
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:09.101 --> 21:13.305
[grunting]

21:14.373 --> 21:18.510
[breathing deeply]

21:47.072 --> 21:48.573
[baby babbling]

21:48.640 --> 21:51.376
[both laughing]

21:51.443 --> 21:54.579
<i>[pleasant music]</i>

21:54.646 --> 21:59.851
<i>♪ ♪</i>
